  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 965994f2c96676e4cb5c993fc6354aab, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  paintingTitle: The White Orchard
  artistName: Vincent van Gogh
  paintingDescription: 'The perspective chosen by Van Gogh guides your gaze upward
    into the tangle of branches. Looking at the painting, you feel as if you are
    in the middle of the flowering trees.

    

    Soon after Van Gogh arrived
    in Arles, the spring came. There were many fruit orchards around the city. He
    enthusiastically painted a large series of studies of orchards in blossom. These
    plum trees were poorly maintained, as their long branches show. Van Gogh was
    especially fond of timeworn trees like these.'
  paintingImage: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 9796225d582c93140919851b10c04619, type: 3}
  orientation: 0
  frameThickness: 0.15
  artworkDepth: 0.04
